  <title>Debugging replica index</title>
  <shortdesc>Description of how to test and verify that the replica index is working.</shortdesc>
  <body>
    <p>It is not easy to test/verify from the outside that the replica index is working. The replica
      index is optional, and it is just an optimization for faster <codeph>stale=false</codeph>
      queries after rebalance. It does not cope with correctness of the results.</p>
    <p>There is a non-public query parameter named <codeph>_type</codeph> used only for debugging
      and testing. Its default value is <codeph>main</codeph>, and the other possible value is
        <codeph>replica</codeph>. </p>
    <p>The following is an example of querying the main (default) and replica indexes on a 2 nodes
      cluster (for the sake of simplicity). Querying the main (normal) index gives this result:</p>
    <codeblock><codeph>&gt; curl -s 'http://localhost:9500/default/_design/test/_view/view1?limit=20&amp;stale=false&amp;debug=true'
